<br>
As to LDoN, its not great, but its has loads of possibilities.  Gear wise, for 3450 points I can put a 1 hander together that is as good as a Acrylia Handled Broadsword (Curse-Smelted Long Blade from guk for 1150, +3 damage from Miragul for 1150, Vampires Kiss from Mistmore for 1150).  The 1450pt armor drops are far better then any armor outside elemental.  Also, you dont need normal grps in LDoN.  A grp of 5 pallys and a bard owns mistmore.  You no longer need a plate class to tank (Rangers w/ decent gear (not elem though) and some def AAs tank fine). <br>
<br>
But LDoN has brought out its share of asses who care about win/loss stats more then anything.  Last night we had a grp about to zone into guk when the rogue got called for a raid.  Everyone in the grp but the mage was all for trying with 5 but the mage was more interested in not having a loss and then left saying he didnt want to be w/ a grp who wanted to loose.  <br>
<br>
Now, the only thing left is to redo the graphics on Butcherblock, South Ro, etc so they are up to par with a zone like JaggedPine.  That way we still have the lag. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=453758">Grendalkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,  Ranger<br>
