<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So pretty much you failed 2 in one night? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I haven't failed anything in LDoN.  I never bothered entering the zones - allowing me to cancel my order.<br>
<br>
<br>
   Quote from Grendalkhan:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Coming from someone who started after luclin came out let me say this. First, Velious is the best expansion there is, not Kunark (Velous just has a lot more depth then Kunark and no 32k HP limits on mobs). Except for expanded bank slots, dyes (which isnt that good of thing when a bright pink ogre runs by), and drogmars, LoY was junk. And Luclin had the possibility of being a great expansion, but wasnt.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm not sure I understand what you are saying here.  Velious came out prior to Luclin, so you weren't playing at that time.  IMO, it's hard to say it's the best expansion if you weren't there to experience what was before it.  Velious had very rich content, but comparatively - it was expected.<br>
<br>
Kunark was something that allowed old school players be excited about something new.  New levels, new spells, new skills, new armor, new zones, our first dungeon that was considered the most dangerous in the game (with no GM assistance) - all for the very first time.  So those of us 2000 people or so per server back in Spring of 2000 - we were really jazzed about the first expansion.  Kunark was a wonderful taste of what we hoped would be the first of many great expansions.  It sincerely left a good feeling in us, that this game's future was boundless.<br>
<br>
Velious was, indeed, very rich.  It taught us to chose our allies within the game.  Extremely good quests and zones for the time.  But to many of us, the thrill wasn't as fresh as it once had been - with Kunark.  Luclin, so-so.  Again, awesome loots and a generally good idea, but sometimes it seemed a little too far fetched and over the edge.  Fun, no doubt.<br>
<br>
Planes of Power was the first expansion to bring back that &quot;old&quot; feeling, for me.  There was, again, a sense of extreme risk... until you discovered your corpse will just pop back at the ZI.  I liked the old days of CRing.  Yeah, coffins can get expensive for an entire raid, but hey - wasn't it SOE who said there was too much plat in the economy in EQ anyway??   PoP allowed small raids, large raids, solo/duo experiences - just like old days.  Or perhaps, it's just that it was an expansion released for high levels - a category I finally fell into.<br>
<br>
LoY - flop, IMO.  I've been to only 2 zones there I think.<br>
<br>
LDoN - too restrictive, and that is my primary complaint.  Yes, I do feel as though individual people are worthy of solo &quot;adventures&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
Or perhaps, all this is just my realization that EQ may finally be taking a more relaxed backseat in my life - my journies here are more rich than anything in EQ.   Perhaps 50 months of EQ has taken it's toll on my discretion - and I'm getting a little bitchy about it.  1520 days.  That's a long ass time <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=265136&resize=true" target="_new"><img border=0 src="http://webpages.charter.net/xynta/xsig25.jpg" </img></a><br>
